Mahavatar Narasimha – 35 Story Cards
Card 1: The Four Kumaras
The Four Kumaras were eternal sages devoted to Lord Vishnu.
Card 2: Jaya and Vijaya’s Curse
Vishnu’s gatekeepers were cursed to be born as demons.
Card 3: Birth of Demon Brothers
They were born as Hiranyaksha and Hiranyakashipu.
Card 4: Varaha Avatar
Vishnu took the Varaha form to defeat Hiranyaksha.
Card 5: Hiranyakashipu’s Revenge
Hiranyakashipu vowed revenge against Vishnu.
Card 6: Severe Penance
He performed intense penance to please Lord Brahma.
Card 7: The Powerful Boon
He received a boon making him nearly invincible.
Card 8: Rise of Tyranny
He declared himself supreme and banned Vishnu worship.
Card 9: Birth of Prahlada
Prahlada was born as a great devotee of Vishnu.
Card 10: Prahlada’s Devotion
Prahlada constantly chanted Vishnu’s name.
Card 11: Teachers’ Failure
His teachers failed to change his faith.
Card 12: Poison Attempt
Prahlada survived poisoning through divine grace.
Card 13: Elephant Attack
He remained unharmed when trampled by elephants.
Card 14: Mountain Fall
He survived being thrown from a cliff.
Card 15: Snake Pit
Venomous snakes could not harm him.
Card 16: Fire Ordeal
Prahlada survived fire through devotion.
Card 17: Holika’s End
Holika burned while Prahlada was saved.
Card 18: The Pillar Question
Hiranyakashipu mocked Vishnu’s presence in a pillar.
Card 19: Narasimha Appears
Vishnu emerged as half-man, half-lion.
Card 20: Twilight Moment
He appeared at dusk, neither day nor night.
Card 21: Palace Threshold
The demon was killed at the doorway.
Card 22: Divine Form
Narasimha was neither man nor beast.
Card 23: The Final Battle
A fierce battle shook the palace.
Card 24: Slaying the Tyrant
Narasimha killed Hiranyakashipu with his claws.
Card 25: Prahlada Protected
Prahlada’s devotion was rewarded.
Card 26: Uncontrolled Fury
Narasimha’s anger shook the universe.
Card 27: Gods Afraid
Even the gods feared his fierce form.
Card 28: Prahlada’s Prayer
Prahlada calmed Narasimha with devotion.
Card 29: Blessings Granted
Prahlada received divine blessings.
Card 30: Restoration of Dharma
Peace and righteousness returned.
Card 31: Symbol of Faith
The story shows devotion conquers evil.
Card 32: Narasimha Jayanti
Devotees celebrate the divine incarnation.
Card 33: Ideal Devotee
Prahlada symbolizes fearless faith.
Card 34: Message of Protection
God protects true devotees.
Card 35: Eternal Victory of Good
Good always triumphs over evil.
